### Executive summary
##### This application is highly important for the business. The cart service maintains state of the customer journey. Issues or outages with this service will directly impact revenue. Any issues should be treated as a priority 2 outage.

### Application Instances
Run the below DQL query to refresh

input.value:
fetch dt.entity.cloud_application_instance, from:now() - 15m
| filter contains(entity.name,"adservice")
| fieldsAdd internalIpAddresses, cloudApplicationInstancePhase, clusterid= clustered_by[`dt.entity.kubernetes_cluster`]
| lookup [fetch dt.entity.kubernetes_cluster| fields entity.name,id],sourceField:clusterid, lookupField:id,prefix:"cluster:"
| fieldsAdd K8sCluster=`cluster:entity.name`, dt.owner= cloudApplicationLabels[dt.owner]
| fieldsRemove clusterid, id, `cluster:entity.name`, `cluster:id`
| filter K8sCluster=="tessier-ashpool"
| expand internalIpAddresses

sections.markdown:
### Start up & shut down procedures

1. Change you kubectl context:
    
    ```kubectl config set-context dumpster-fire-cluster```

1. Recycle pods:

    ```kubectl delete pod -n dt-boutique -l=app=adservice```

### Health checks

[Dumpster Fire App Home Page](https://dumpsterfire.app)

[Ad Service Workload - Dynatrace](https://bwm98081.apps.dynatrace.com/ui/apps/dynatrace.classic.kubernetes.workloads/ui/entity/CLOUD_APPLICATION-5EF6242A9B684D7B)
supporting services

### Historical Issues

- [Dynatrace know issues for Ad Service](https://bwm98081.apps.dynatrace.com/ui/apps/dynatrace.classic.problems/ui/problems?gtf=-90d+to+now&gf=all&entityId=CLOUD_APPLICATION-5EF6242A9B684D7B)
- [Jira Issue Filter for Production Ad Service](https://kdtharrington.atlassian.net/browse/INC-9198?jql=labels%20%3D%20adservice)

### troubleshooting steps

1. Run the below DQL queries and ensure logs are streaming for logs
1. Verify ALL pods are running in the cluster via above 
1. [Review Argo CD for deployment issues](https://argofys.com/applications?showFavorites=false&proj=&sync=&autoSync=&health=&namespace=&cluster=&labels=)
1. If not, pods can be force recycled (see start up & shutdown procedures)
1. If none of the above work, reach out to on-call
1. Document all and steps taken and incident timeline via JIRA

input.value:
fetch logs
| filter ((not matchesValue(event.type, "k8s") or isNull(event.type)) and (in(dt.entity.cloud_application_instance, classicEntitySelector("type(CLOUD_APPLICATION_INSTANCE), toRelationships.IS_KUBERNETES_SVC_OF_CAI(type(KUBERNETES_SERVICE),entityId(KUBERNETES_SERVICE-EA0FB0D47791BB57))")) or in(dt.entity.kubernetes_service, classicEntitySelector("type(KUBERNETES_SERVICE),entityId(KUBERNETES_SERVICE-EA0FB0D47791BB57)"))))
| sort timestamp desc
